It's the liver.

30:13.950 --> 30:14.985
What do you want to do?

30:15.123 --> 30:16.953
- Uh, Pringle maneuver.
- Bedside?

30:17.091 --> 30:18.230
Atraumatic clamps, please.

30:18.368 --> 30:20.819
Yasuda, put your hand
where my hand is.

30:20.957 --> 30:22.303
You're gonna hold
the bleeding here

30:22.441 --> 30:25.064
while Wilson clamps
the blood flow to the liver.

30:25.202 --> 30:27.239
Then I will try
and control the bleeding.

30:27.377 --> 30:28.343
Come on, come on.
Follow my hand.

30:28.481 --> 30:30.518
Okay.
Yeah. Here, I'll help.

30:30.656 --> 30:32.002
- Alright, alright.
- Like that?

30:32.140 --> 30:33.245
Exactly like that.

30:33.383 --> 30:34.660
- Okay, go, Wilson.
- Okay.

30:34.798 --> 30:36.731
Hepatoduodenal ligament
is clamped.

30:36.869 --> 30:38.629
Okay, good.
O-chromic liver suture.

30:38.767 --> 30:40.631
Great. Okay, alright.

30:40.769 --> 30:42.012
Alright, I'm going deep.

30:43.772 --> 30:44.635
I see it.

30:47.984 --> 30:49.192
Okay, pressure's climbing.

30:51.125 --> 30:52.402
Okay, scissors.

30:57.579 --> 30:59.581
Okay, let's pack her
- and get a new wound vac.
- Okay.

30:59.719 --> 31:01.687
